To fix this issue we can check if the bracket `(` exists and if it is the first letter in table name, then return it without quote. It will not quote the expressions witch starts with `(` but quote table names with brackets like `table_name(1)` etc. 

To do this trick we just need to replace `false` to `0` like this:
```php
if (strpos($name, '(') !== 0 || strpos($name, '{{') !== false) {
```

Or we can add additional check to latest bracket and separate it from `{{` checking like this:

```php
if (strpos($name, '(') === 0 && strpos($name, ')') === strlen($name) - 1) {
    return $name;
}
if (strpos($name, '{{') !== false) {
    return $name;
}
```
